ves.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"False positives here often come from real PR lifecycle semantics (open/merged states, branch linkage) at external contract boundaries, not just local branching logic. Integration might test wiring, but real-state/API interpretation failures are System-level. Rejected higher levels: no AI/ML output dependency or multi-agent sequencing in behavior text.","test_description":"Use branches mapped to real/open and real/merged PR cases, run staleness detection through its normal git+PR integration path, and assert classification is not stale-no-PR in both cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.64,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed stale work.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This failure mode is fundamentally about real git graph transformations (rebase/squash hash rewrite) and reachability outcomes, which require actual VCS behavior. In-process fakes often miss these topology details, so MOCK-HIDE/REAL-INFRA push to System. Rejected higher levels: behavior contains no model judgment or chained agentic steps.","test_description":"Construct real git scenarios covering rebase and squash merge transitions, execute the detector after each transition, and assert stale-no-PR clears once work is incorporated despite commit hash changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
